        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-21 16:05:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThis change us only hiding the problem, not really fixing it. There should be a check in the kernel that limits the user to the maximum bio size and avoid causing the oops, rather than just checking this in the script. The script doesn't know how the kernel is configured, and there may be different scripts trying to exercise this code. It should never be possible for userspace to trigger an oops in the kernel.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    }
